Kubernetes Backup
│
├─ 1. Backup Scope
│   ├─ etcd Data
│   │   └─ Cluster state, configmaps, secrets, CRDs
│   ├─ Persistent Volumes (PV)
│   │   ├─ Block storage
│   │   └─ File storage
│   ├─ Namespaces / Resources
│   │   ├─ Deployments, Services
│   │   ├─ ConfigMaps, Secrets
│   │   └─ Custom Resources (CRDs)
│   └─ Cluster Metadata
│       ├─ RBAC
│       └─ Network Policies
│
├─ 2. Backup Methods
│   ├─ etcd Snapshots
│   │   ├─ Built-in etcdctl snapshot
│   │   └─ Automated cron snapshots
│   ├─ Volume Snapshots
│   │   ├─ CSI VolumeSnapshot
│   │   └─ Cloud-provider snapshots (AWS EBS, GCP PD, Azure Disk)
│   ├─ Resource Export
│   │   ├─ kubectl get -o yaml/json
│   │   └─ GitOps repository (configuration as code)
│   └─ Full Cluster Backup Tools
│       ├─ Velero
│       ├─ Kasten K10
│       └─ Stash by AppsCode
│
├─ 3. Backup Storage Options
│   ├─ Object Storage
│   │   ├─ S3 / MinIO
│   │   ├─ GCS
│   │   └─ Azure Blob
│   ├─ Network Storage
│   │   ├─ NFS
│   │   └─ SMB
│   └─ Local Storage
│       └─ Node disk snapshots
│
├─ 4. Recovery / Restore
│   ├─ Disaster Recovery
│   │   ├─ Cluster recreation
│   │   └─ Cross-region restore
│   ├─ Namespace / Resource Restore
│   │   ├─ Selective restore
│   │   └─ Application-level restore
│   ├─ Volume Restore
│   │   ├─ CSI restore
│   │   └─ Cloud snapshot restore
│   └─ Validation
│       ├─ Test restore regularly
│       └─ DR drills
│
├─ 5. Automation & Scheduling
│   ├─ CronJobs
│   ├─ Backup policies
│   │   ├─ Retention
│   │   ├─ Versioning
│   │   └─ Incremental / differential backup
│   └─ Alerts / Monitoring
│       ├─ Backup success/failure notifications
│       └─ Metrics tracking
│
└─ 6. Best Practices
    ├─ Backup etcd frequently
    ├─ Use off-cluster storage for redundancy
    ├─ Encrypt backups at rest and in transit
    ├─ Automate restores and test regularly
    ├─ Use consistent snapshot mechanisms for PVs
    └─ Integrate backups with GitOps and CI/CD pipelines
